    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="801"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.21112 RP/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>393. See my A–178, February 26, noon. This morning Folsom, Rubin<note n="96"
                        xml:id="d801fn96">Seymour J. Rubin, Assistant Chief, Division of Financial
                        and Monetary Affairs.</note> and I had meeting with Minister of Education
                    who has been designated by Acting President Echandía to deal with replacement
                        <pb facs="0853" n="839" xml:id="pg_839"/> program. Dr. Rocha said that as
                    Minister of Hacienda and Minister of Public Health<note n="97" xml:id="d801fn97"
                        >Jorge E. Gaitan.</note> are leaving office next week to enter presidential
                    campaign administrative action with regard to nationalization of German drug
                    industry probably cannot take place until early April. On the return of
                        Derby<note n="98" xml:id="d801fn98">Robert J. Derby, Special Assistant to
                        the Ambassador in Colombia.</note> from Mexico City however Dr. Rocha
                    indicated willingness to discuss matter with him and it was suggested by me that
                    Folsom and Rubin stop in Bogotá on their return trip from Chile to acquaint
                    themselves more fully with situation.</p>
                <p>Dr. Rocha made it clear that because of the political situation no constructive
                    steps may be expected for some weeks.</p>
                <p>Rocha said that the question of replacement program would have to be submitted to
                    the National Defense Commission prior to administrative action being taken by
                    the Minister of Hacienda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
